  "summary": "PoC package executes attacker-controlled shell command via postinstall hook",
  "details": "package.json declares a postinstall lifecycle script that runs a shell command during `npm install`, writing a marker file `/tmp/pwned.txt` containing the string `PWNED_BY_DEEPLINK`. The package self-labels as a proof-of-compromise demonstration with no legitimate functionality (described only as 'test'). While the current payload is a benign marker write, the package establishes arbitrary shell command execution on the installer's machine at install time as its sole purpose, and serves as a template/demonstration of installer-side RCE via npm lifecycle scripts.",
